It's unfortunately an often occurrence that communication with central Jira can break down in a number of ways. Often times this can happen while filling out data, like issue descriptions and comments, the contents of which become lost after being presented with a service error or a 500 "Service Temporarily Unavailable". In some cases many paragraphs of work can be lost, and for both myself and those who have been in this situation, it's extremely frustrating. I have began to get in the habbit of selecting all of the content, and coping it to the clipboard every single time I write a description or comment.

I'd like to propose some mechanism to protect that content when a user is ready and take action to persist to the server. The most affected area is likely Jira Comments. Any ability to recover there would be a quick win. A likely approach might be to copy the content, or model to local storage, and allow recovery when Jira is accessible again. At worst case, some sort of "Save content to Clipboard" checkbox might work.

